                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>that its remarks are as pertinent now as when delivered. News\n                                        from<lb/> here I can send you but little, A friend who\n                                        lately paid us a visit, and still<lb/> more lately visits\n                                                  <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> (I believe) is\n                                        pleased to say \"altho we Canadians do not<lb/> form (here)\n                                        one of the largest and most influential congregations we\n                                        prove that<lb/> we sufficiently understand what is [?] to\n                                        the respectability of Synagogue worship<lb/> \"The building\n                                        is most striking for its very neat pretty appearance, marked\n                                        decorum<lb/> pervaded the assembled, and an utter absence of\n                                        that boisterousness, sometimes<lb/> unfortunately prevailing\n                                        in our larger Synagogues was observable xxx The prayers<lb/>\n                                        were read by the [Hebrew] <add>[?]</add> with an apparent\n                                        desire to avoid that style which<lb/> reminds one so much of\n                                        the opera and which for time and place is alike<lb/>\n                                        objectionable xxxx It must be highly gratifying to you to\n                                        know that your<lb/> discourses, and general services as\n                                        reader and teacher are highly spoken of (dont[?]<lb/> you\n                                        think dear friend I have some excuse if I grow vain?) My\n                                        friend ([?]) continues,<lb/> But what pleased me most was to\n                                        see your pupil (Mouther[?] I <persName>Ascher the son<lb/>\n                                                  of the Parnass</persName>) called us\n                                                  <persName>Maphlir[?]</persName>, The very correct\n                                        and pleasing name of<lb/> his reading afforded me much\n                                        pleasure.\" If you wish to give us all a fond<lb/> character\n                                        here you can insert it in your news Items. The name of the\n                                        writer (tho'<lb/> perhaps known to you shall be provided if\n                                        you require it editorially tho'<lb/> I am not sure he would\n                                        like it (his name) to appear in the Occident for All he says\n                                        is–\"If<lb/> you choose, write <persName>Mr Leeser</persName>\n                                        what a <hi rend=\"underline\">first rate</hi> character\n                                        stranger gives<lb/> you.\" All the news I can give you of us\n                                        (should you pronounce that <hi rend=\"underline\">no</hi><lb/>\n                                        news) is that our Parnas is <persName>Mr Ascher</persName>\n                                        whose inde[?]able services as Parnas, and<lb/> whose jealous\n                                        endeavors to promote the welfare and quiet of the\n                                        community<lb/> with his <sic>colleage</sic>\n                                        <persName>Dr David</persName>\n                                        <del>the</del> President are mentioned by all in the\n                                        highest<lb/> terms. They all have been unanimously\n                                        re-elected. The formation[?] of the new Board of Trustees\n                                        has <del>also</del> caused general satisfaction<lb/> among\n                                                  <del>to</del> the members. These are\n                                                  <persName>Messrs S. Benjamin</persName>,\n                                                  <persName>Simon Hart</persName>, and\n                                                  <persName>Jesse Joseph</persName>,<lb/> Treasurer\n                                                  <persName>John Levy</persName> (re-elected) and\n                                                  <persName>Levy Myer Solomons</persName> (also\n                                        re-elected.) During<lb/> the late summer an unprecedented[?]\n                                        number of German Jewish Emigrants visited<lb/>\n                                        <placeName>Canada</placeName>, Indigent, and in many cases\n                                        sick! They provide most services<lb/> drain on the funds of\n                                        our Infant Philanthropic Society, About Thirty<lb/>\n                                        unfortunate persons many with families besides one\n                                        noatbly[?] pensioner, were<lb/> recipients. On [?] that the\n                                        committee contemplated a Benefit Ball<lb/> but have not yet\n                                        held any [?] of [?]. Should they determine<lb/> upon this,\n                                        they will no doubt make it known in the Occident.<lb/> This\n                                        dear friend is all the news I can scrape together\n                                        concerning<lb/> our precious selves, and I have preferred\n                                        giving you most of it as<lb/> an \"Extract from a private\n                                        communication\" because if I had myself</p>"
                  },
