                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>undertaken to \"give characters\" I should altho' finding much to\n                                        praise<lb/> still find a little to censure–But to other\n                                        matters. I received last<lb/> week a letter from my friend\n                                                  <persName>D Benisk</persName> now Editor of the\n                                        Voice of Jews<lb/> He writes me that it is to be\n                                        considerably enlarged and the whole to be<lb/> under his\n                                        management. This last would imply, strange fingers in the\n                                        Free<lb/> and I think this has been the case with the late\n                                        [?] articles contend<lb/> in the Voice. In a letter received\n                                        from my father the same mail he writes<lb/> \"I hear that it\n                                        is the intention of your friend <persName>Mr\n                                                  Leeser</persName> to visit old<lb/>\n                                        <placeName>England</placeName>–Do you know whether this is\n                                        really the case, I should be most<lb/> happy to have it in\n                                        my power to exercise my great esteem for him.\"<lb/> What am\n                                        I to reply, dear friend? I hear this for the fist time.\n                                        He<lb/> encloses me a prospectus of\n                                                  <persName>Mayer's</persName> projected\n                                        publication–What do<lb/> you think of this. There is no\n                                        doubt I should say that as far as abilities,<lb/> Rabbinical\n                                        and general knowledge so, there is not a man, christian or\n                                        Jew<lb/> who is better able to answer <persName>Mr\n                                                  C[?]</persName> than this said\n                                                  <persName>Hoya</persName>. As a<lb/> Hebraist he\n                                        has not I firmly believe his equal. Witness his\n                                        [Hebrew]<lb/> and Hebrew Translation of <persName>Mr\n                                                  Cauls</persName> Old Paths. Some attribute<lb/>\n                                        the Heb version of the Christian Common Prayer to him but\n                                        looking<lb/> at the style of that sublime composition I\n                                        should doubt this much<lb/> His last articles too in the\n                                                  <placeName>London</placeName> Jewish Chronicle\n                                        are–to make<lb/> use of a mysterious old saying \"not to be\n                                        sneezed at. I am more<lb/> anxious to see his 1st no. The\n                                        [?] of state [?] I suppose has<lb/> retired purposely to\n                                        make room for the \"faithful missionary\" who<lb/> will\n                                        doubtless occupy much room on the tables of the\n                                        religious<lb/> reading world, but the Jewish Christian,\n                                        altho' the same apathy<lb/> unfortunately exist to [?]\n                                        [Hebrew] here, as on the subject of an<lb/> efficient\n                                        ministry. With respect to this last the observation<lb/> of\n                                        my father very often seems occurs to me. He very dryly\n                                        observed one day<lb/> \"The [Hebrew] to sail them must be\n                                        [Hebrew] [?]\"<lb/> and I think he is right. But I sincerely\n                                        hope this unhealthy<lb/> state of things will give way to\n                                        more worthy [?] notions<lb/> It has done so in many cases\n                                        let us hope that its <sic>observence</sic><lb/> will soon be\n                                        universal.</p>\n                              <p>I informed <persName>Mrs Ascher</persName> of your invitation not\n                                        to charge for<lb/> the nos, and she denies to acknowledge\n                                        your politeness–</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p39883d25/canvas/p3"
