                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p39883d25/manifest/annotation/p4",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>So you are a reformer. I have not yet seen your\n                                                  <date>November</date> number<lb/> but doubt well\n                                        that the reforms there propounded will shock<lb/> orthodox\n                                        susceptibility but little, and that they are of a\n                                        practiced<lb/> and [?]. I too am a reformer as far as\n                                        endeavours<lb/> which I believe to be <hi rend=\"underline\"\n                                                  >consistent</hi> and legal, in improving the\n                                        manner<lb/> of Synagogue worship are concerned. I don't\n                                        think the cause of<lb/> orthodoxy would suffer much did\n                                        conservative Synagogues introduce<lb/> quiet respectability\n                                        in their services. Orthodoxy by nature<lb/> by age, and by\n                                        character is respectable. Absurd and inconsistent<lb/>\n                                        novelty in the Synagogue is disrefutable in its very\n                                        essence<lb/> and it appears therefore a serious cruel\n                                        anomaly that while<lb/> all that care [?] devotional\n                                        feelings prevail in the new [?]<lb/> in the old, very much\n                                        that is calculated to excite disgust<lb/> worldly and impure\n                                        feelings is there observable. But my dear<lb/> friend\n                                        [Hebrew], continue to sound in the unwilling ears<lb/> of\n                                        the [Hebrew], and [?] success <hi rend=\"underline\">must</hi>\n                                        one day follow.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\"Prata albicaul camis friunis\" Our Canadian\n                                        winter<lb/> approaches in the shape of a few slight snow\n                                        storms. See too<lb/> looks more plentiful in the streets\n                                        than it did in summer, But<lb/> with all its severity\n                                        speaking from last winters experienced<lb/> I like the\n                                        winter here much. There is a [?] the cold [?]<lb/> clearness\n                                        of atmosphere that renders the season here much more<lb/>\n                                        agreeable and healthy than in\n                                        <placeName>London</placeName>.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I must now bid you good bye dear friend for<lb/>\n                                        the present. Hoping you will write me very soon, and<lb/>\n                                        [?] and that you may receive this [Hebrew]!</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(6)\">I am My dear Friend</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(6)\">Yours very sincerely</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(6)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">Abraham deSola</persName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p><persName>Mrs Joseph</persName> daughters desire</p>\n                              <p>me to remember them to you</p>\n                              <p>with comforts.</p>\n                    </body>\n          </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p39883d25/canvas/p4"
